File:Â Former President Jacob Zuma is calling on South Africans from all walks of life to share their stories about him. JOHANNESBURG - Jacob Zuma is known for being a shrewd politician, a doting father and even a singer. But what about an author?
The former president is calling on South Africans from all walks of life to share their stories about him. The Jacob G. Zuma Foundation is compiling a book on his impact on generations of ordinary South Africans and leaders. WATCH: Zuma threatens to dish the dirt The foundation says it welcomes pictures and contributions about Zuma's influence on people's successes. Zuma said on Twitter that he is "quite excited" about the project.